{
  "stem": "4963.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it was-- I think ORT had-- somehow, they had gotten money from ORT to establish schools.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the Germans did permit that on the pretext that we were going to be-- that they were going to teach us a trade that would benefit the, the workforce.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I was in a sewing class.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My cousin Wolf went with me, and he was in carpentry and plumbing.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We would take various classes but nothing of educational nature, nothing of, you know, of math or, or history or languages-- nothing like that.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were only permitted to do trade teachings.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So that was not far from the house.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I remember we used to go over there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And things were-- every day was an eventful day because there were all kinds of happenings every single day as far as, as far as separating people and dwindling-- you know, killing off people.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And there was the [NON-ENGLISH] and the big Aktion and the [NON-ENGLISH], children's Aktion, old people Aktion.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, I remember that in our house-- actually, under my Aunt Paula's bedroom, under a couch, there was what we called a [NON-ENGLISH], a, a hiding place, that my uncle built, my Uncle Osher.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And what it consisted of was we would pull the couch out.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And there was a great big cover.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And under the cover was like a little basement, a little hole in the ground.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we had it all equipped with food, with water, and some food and light-- flashlights.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so whenever there was a rumor out that there was another Aktion, another separation in, in the works, we would many times go into this [NON-ENGLISH], into this hiding place.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we would stay there, sometimes for several days until, until the panic was over.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
